\CheapTitle{The Centroid of a Triangle}

\begin{dfn}#[Median#]
Let $A$, $B$, and $C$ be distinct points. If $M$ is the midpoint of $\Segment{B}{C}$, then $\Line{A}{M}$ is called the \emph{median} of $\Triangle{A}{B}{C}$ through $A$.
\end{dfn}

Every triangle has precisely three medians; one for each vertex.

